cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS

This paper is primarily focused on the theoretical understanding of neural networks, specifically those with one hidden layer. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the importance of symmetry in the design of neural networks, which suggests that it may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the empirical verification of the results may make it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
